0 Newbie Helper~
Newbie helpers (denoted by an H in the HR* in the who display) are usually 
very experienced players who will take it upon themselves to assist new players 
as needed, so that they can better get along in the mud. The object is to teach 
the newbies so that they may do things themselves or teach others. Newbie helper 
flags are granted to mortals by the immortals this is not a flag you can put up and 
take down.They are empowered to create Newbie Kits (Newbie Helpers type Newbie to 
create one) for newbies as needed, as well as to go into the MUD School to "show 
them the ropes". NO OTHER MORTAL PLAYER CAN DO THIS! At times, the Newbie Helper  may 
render other assistance, like spells and finding equipment.

1. Newbie Helpers generally do their job via imparting bits of supplemental 
information. This means that they may fill in pieces of the puzzle for 
newbies .. Newbie Helpers may or may not, at their option, spell newbies 
up. {CIf you are a newbie please understand that spell ups are not an obligation 
they are a gift and you should thank the person spelling you up.{x

2. NH assistance is only intended as a SUPPLEMENT for player efforts, not a 
substitute. This means that Helpers may lend the occasional helping hand and 
coaching but they will not do all the work; contrary to what some people 
seem to think everyone is STILL responsible for their own successes and 
failures. Newbie Helpers are more than welcome to lend a hand upon request, 
but we do ask that they not make a habit of doing all the work; this can 
lead to mooching and newbie helpers are not doing anyone a favor by playing the 
game for them.. Your duties do not excuse anyone from earning their own crust.

One other thing to remember: those of you who are Newbie Helpers must remember 
that people look up to you. Therefore, do your best to be friendly and courteous 
with other people, especially newbies. Whether you like to think of it that way or not, 
you ARE rolemodels for the mud to see. So, please make sure that your advice is as good 
as you can make it; treat others with respect; show them the proper uses of channels, eq etc. 
do NOT act better than... we have all been newbies at one time or another. In short, just be 
the nice friendly mortals we know you are. And by all means do NOT ignore newbies completely. 
If you are busy at least respond letting them know your busy.

{WNote to newbies: Please remember that these players are also playing the game. They may not 
always have time right when you want it. And remember that pestering them for things will only 
cause them to ignore you or resent their flag.{x
~

0 SKILLS SPELLS~
The {Cskills{x and {Cspells{x commands are used to display your character's list
of available {Cskills{x (or {Cspells{x, as the case may be).  They are listed in
order of level, with {Ymana cost{x (for {Cspells{x) or {Ypercentage{x (for {Cskills{x)
listed where applicable. See {YHELP SPELLS{x for details on the {CSPELLS{x command.

If you want to see the levels at which various skills and spells are
*potentially* available to you, type {CLEVELS{x class-name. Example:
{Clevels warrior{x will show you the levels at which warriors get skills
and spells. You can substitute any other class.
~

0 SKILLS SPELLS~
The {Cskills{x and {Cspells{x commands tell you about the skills and spells
you have, will have or could gain. Here are some things you can do with it:

{Cspells{x        -- gives you a list of all the spells for which you have
                 gained the spell groups, and the levels at which you got
                 them or will get them.
{Cspells 75{x     -- lists all spells in your spell groups from level 75 up.
{Cspells 10 20{x  -- lists all spells in your spell groups from level 10
                 to 20 inclusive.
{Cspells c{x      -- lists ALL spells starting with C, including two-word
		 spell names whose 2nd word starts with a 'C'
{Cspells breath{x -- lists all breath spells.
{Cspells weather{x - lists all the spells in the {CWEATHER{x group. You must
                 give the full name of the group for this to work.
{Cspells groups{x -- lists all available spell groups, showing which ones
                 you already have.

All but the first and last of these variations display output in a new,
colorful and more informative format which tells you not only how much
mana the spell costs but also how skilled you are at it. For spells which
are not in any spell group you have gained, it shows you this fact too.
~

