0 BOW ARROW RANGED ARCHERY SHOOT~
Syntax: {Cshoot {g<{Ydistance.direction{g> <{Ytarget{g>

This command allows you to fire your bow at a creature in another room.
Your {Ytarget{x should be the name of the creature you wish to shoot. 
{YDirection{x may be north, south, east, west, up, or down.  To shoot
farther than the next room, use {C2.{x or {C3.{x

Examples:
{C   shoot              {g- shoot your current opponent with your bow.
{C   shoot fido         {g- shoot a fido right here.
{C   shoot north fido   {g- shoot the nearest fido to the north.
{C   shoot 2.north fido {g- shoot the fido 2 rooms to the north.
{C   shoot 3.north fido {g- shoot the fido 3 rooms to the north.

Be warned that most creatures react negatively to being shot.
~

