0 LOOT DYNAMIC PREFIX SUFFIX~
Legacy now has a dynamic loot system in place. This means that
you are no longer constrained by what the areas have built into
them in terms of equipment and weapons.

How it works:
On killing a monster that rewards you exp, there is a chance
that a piece of eq will be created on the spot. This piece of 
equipment will be placed in the corpse of the monster so it is
important that you have autoloot set to on.


The equipment and stats on the equipment will roll based on your
character's level. There are some base stats (such as hp, mana,
stam, hitroll and damroll) that have a chance of rolling. 

There are 4 Qualities the equipment can roll:
 Normal
 {x({GUn{Hcomm{Gon{x){x
 {x({BR{Nar{Be{x){x
 {x({CLe{Tge{gn{Tda{Cry{x){x
 
Beginning at {x({GUn{Hcomm{Gon{x){x, a piece can roll a {Rprefix{x.
These prefixes will add additional power to the piece of gear.
An example would be a {x({GUn{Hcomm{Gon{x){x Sword rolls 
{CM{Ba{Ng{Mi{Nc{Ba{Cl{x. This {Rprefix{x will add between 41 to 
75 mana to the piece of gear. {x({GUn{Hcomm{Gon{x){x can roll 
{R1 prefix{x, {x({BR{Nar{Be{x){x can roll {R2 prefixes{x, and 
{x({CLe{Tge{gn{Tda{Cry{x){x can roll {R3 prefixes{x. These
prefixes can be seen when you {Vlore{x or {Yidentify{x the
gear.

At qualities of {x({BR{Nar{Be{x){x and higher, a piece of gear
can roll 1 {Rsuffix{x. These suffixes bestow powerful affects to
the gear including the ability to lower the mana cost of a spell,
or increase your spell or weapon damage. These suffixes can also 
be seen when you {Vlore{x or {Yidentify{x the gear as well.
